You are here:

Create an Optimization (Beta)

Use Decision Optimization to optimize the recommendations of your Einstein Discovery models by creating an Optimization. Optimizations improve Einstein Discovery suggestions by incorporating business rules, objectives, and constraints.

Select a Model (Beta)
The first step is to select the model to optimize recommendations for.
Define Optimization Objective (Beta)
The second step is to define the objective, which is the company goal or variable to optimize recommendations for.
Configure Decision Optimization (Beta)
The third step is to configure the model's recommendation by adding constraints and limits.
Filter Which Records to Optimize (Beta)
The fourth step is to add an optional filter to control which records use the optimization results.
Review and Save Results (Beta)
The fifth and final step is to review and save your new optimization.
